Transamerica Corp's TransamericaInsurance Co said it signed a definitive pact to buy a 51 pctinterest in Sedgwick Group PLC's River Thames Insurance Co.    Transamerica will buy 11 mln newly issued Class A shares ofRiver Thames for 2.23 dlrs per share.    Sedgwick wil retain a 49 pct interest in River Thames,which is a property liability reinsurer.    The agreement, subject to shareholder approval, is expectedto close by the end of the year, the company said.    In 1986, River Thames reported net premiums written of 36mln dlrs. Reuter&#3;